  field_id:"unpackedSogoRunnyMixtureSoluteglazingInstruction",
  instruction:"SOGO glazes do not contain glue or other binders. It's normal for them to be quite powdery. Be careful when handling glazed work.

  Overly powdery glazes can also indicate a glaze that's too deflocculated. Be sure to check the viscosity with a flow cup. If it's too low and the flow time is too short, you'll need to thicken the glaze with a saturated solution of Epsom salts.",
  section_id:{{section_id }}
%}

